== Results ==

=== What does a heat map mean? ===

If your search matches more than one gene, the results will be displayed in a heatmap. All the genes found are listed in the first column of the heatmap, the
 remaining columns show the conditions. The heatmap entries provide the number of experiments in which a gene was observed to be significantly over-expressed (red heatmap cell)
 or under-expressed (blue) in the corresponding condition.  See the [http://www.ebi.ac.uk/training/online/course/arrayexpress-investigating-gene-expression-pattern-0 train online] document for more detail.  

